  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Technical Assistance for the implementation of the Public Infrastructure Coordinating Unit and the Central American and Caribbean Games in Panama</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The XXIV Central American and Caribbean Games will take place in Panama City in 2022. Therefore, the Government of Panama City, has assumed financial, programmatic and organizational commitments that govern the events and involved the Project Infrastructure Coordinating Unit, supported by UNOPS to assist with the four large programmatic blocks, namely: Organization, Sports Infrastructure, Athlete Management and Financial Management and sustainability.  UNOPS helps structure a project management framework that ensures its implementation and helps deliver for the conceptual infrastructure designs, engineering and architectural work  of seven civil sports works through the Public Infrastructure Coordinating Unit in Panama.</narrative>
  </description>
